  "prompt": "What countries participate in The Commonwealth Games?",
  "response": "The Commonwealth Games involves countries and territories that are part of the Commonwealth of Nations, which mostly consists of former British colonies. Some of the participating countries include:\n\n1. United Kingdom\n2. Canada\n3. Australia\n4. New Zealand\n5. India\n6. South Africa\n7. Nigeria\n8. Jamaica\n9. Kenya\n10. Malaysia\n11. Singapore\n12. Pakistan\n13. Bangladesh\n14. Sri Lanka\n15. Uganda\n16. Ghana\n17. Cameroon\n18. Zimbabwe\n19. Barbados\n20. Trinidad and Tobago\n\nThis list is not exhaustive, as the Commonwealth includes around 56 countries, most of which can participate in the Games. The number of participating countries can vary slightly from one Games to another.\n\nThe Games are held every four years, featuring multi-sport events where athletes from Commonwealth nations compete, promoting friendship and athletic excellence among member countries.",
